{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, to confirm our hypothesis that text generated from fine-tuned models is harder to detect for both humans and machines, we run an online human annotation study.",
    "Full methodological details are available in the Appendix E, but in summary: we recruited 250 human participants on Amazon Mechanical Turk to categorize tweets as either AIgenerated or human-written.",
    "In two separate studies, AI-generated tweets were obtained from either the base GPT4o model (3,640 human annotations) or the fine-tuned (large sample) GPT4o model (3,360 human annotations), and detection accuracy is compared across the two conditions.",
    "Ethics approval for this study was obtained from the Research Ethics Board of the National Research Council of Canada.",
    "The purpose of our linguistic analysis is to determine whether the texts that are generated by LLMs are significantly different from those written by humans."
  ]
}